article.headline: Houston 84, North Texas 51
article.story: HOUSTON -- Kelvin Lewis scored 20 points and grabbed nine rebounds to lead Houston to an 84-51 win over North Texas on Saturday night. Marcus Cousin added 18 points and Aubrey Coleman had 13 for the Cougars (4-1), who outscored North Texas 50-23 in the second half to pull away. Collin Dennis scored 12 points to lead North Texas (4-2). Tristan Thompson added 11. The Cougars shot 45 percent from the field while North Texas struggled, hitting just 18 of 60 shots.
